9#include "libANGLE/LoggingAnnotator.h"
10
11#include "libANGLE/trace.h"

13namespace angle
14{
15
16bool LoggingAnnotator::getStatus()
17{
18 return false;
19}
20
21void LoggingAnnotator::beginEvent(gl::Context *context,
22 gl::EntryPoint entryPoint,
23 const char *eventName,
24 const char *eventMessage)
25{
26 ANGLE_TRACE_EVENT_BEGIN0("gpu.angle", eventName);
27}
28
29void LoggingAnnotator::endEvent(gl::Context *context,
30 const char *eventName,
31 gl::EntryPoint entryPoint)
32{
33 ANGLE_TRACE_EVENT_END0("gpu.angle", eventName);
34}
35
36void LoggingAnnotator::setMarker(const char *markerName)
37{
38 ANGLE_TRACE_EVENT_INSTANT0("gpu.angle", markerName);
39}
40
41void LoggingAnnotator::logMessage(const gl::LogMessage &msg) const
42{
43 auto *plat = ANGLEPlatformCurrent();
44 if (plat != nullptr)
45 {
46 switch (msg.getSeverity())
47 {
48 case gl::LOG_FATAL:
49 case gl::LOG_ERR:
50 plat->logError(plat, msg.getMessage().c_str());
51 break;
52 case gl::LOG_WARN:
53 plat->logWarning(plat, msg.getMessage().c_str());
54 break;
55 case gl::LOG_INFO:
56 plat->logInfo(plat, msg.getMessage().c_str());
57 break;
58 default:
59 UNREACHABLE();
60 }
61 }
62 gl::Trace(msg.getSeverity(), msg.getMessage().c_str());
63}
